+# GitHub publication collision guard — 0276-r4
+
+R4 completes the preflight required by r3. It reads the issue, compares the
+expected revision against `updated_at`, ETag or a canonical snapshot digest,
+blocks closed issues by default, and searches for the deterministic publication
+marker. Label replacement uses current-versus-desired labels as its replay test.
+
+Statuses are `clear`, `idempotent_replay`, `conflict` or `blocked`. Only `clear`
+may reach the adapter. Replay returns success semantics without another HTTP
+mutation.
+
+A CLI is included for the configured test. Its default mode is `plan`.
+`preflight` and `apply` read `AUTODOC_GITHUB_TOKEN` from the environment; the
+token is never accepted as an argument or printed.
+
+The first live test should target a disposable issue and begin with plan, then
+preflight, then apply after checking the exact expected revision.
