+# GitHub controlled publication test — after 0276-r4
+
+## Repository configuration
+
+1. Create a disposable issue in the target repository.
+2. Create a fine-grained token with the minimum Issues write permission needed
+   for the selected operation.
+3. Export it only in the shell:
+
+```bash
+export AUTODOC_GITHUB_TOKEN='...'
+```
+
+Do not place the token in JSON, Git, shell history or test fixtures.
+
+## Prepare files
+
+Create an approved review JSON and a command JSON. The command must contain the
+current issue `updated_at`, ETag or snapshot digest in `expected_remote_revision`.
+Keep `execute=false` for plan/preflight. Set `execute=true`,
+`operator_confirmed=true` and `remote_mutation_enabled=true` only for apply.
+
+## Sequence
+
+```bash
+PYTHONPATH=src:. python tools/run_github_controlled_publication_smoke_0276.py \
+  --command-json /secure/path/command.json \
+  --review-json /secure/path/review.json \
+  --mode plan
+
+PYTHONPATH=src:. python tools/run_github_controlled_publication_smoke_0276.py \
+  --command-json /secure/path/command.json \
+  --review-json /secure/path/review.json \
+  --mode preflight
+
+PYTHONPATH=src:. python tools/run_github_controlled_publication_smoke_0276.py \
+  --command-json /secure/path/command.json \
+  --review-json /secure/path/review.json \
+  --mode apply
+```
+
+Run apply only when preflight reports `status=clear`. Re-running the same command
+must report `idempotent_replay` and perform no second mutation.
